Package: xtop
Version: 0.41.1-1
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: libc6
Recommends: postgresql, journalctl
Installed-Size: 23400
Maintainer: Farhan Tahir <farhan.003@gmail.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/ftahirops/xtop
Description: Incident-first root-cause analysis console for Linux
 xtop is a terminal-based system monitor with ranked root-cause hypotheses,
 evidence scoring, and eBPF deep diagnostics. v0.41.1 polishes the setup
 wizard: prompts for which interface to bind when multiple NICs are
 present, prints one IP-based join URL per interface (labeled LAN / WAN /
 container / wireguard), and drops the SSH-tunnel instructions.
